l release of Neverwinter Nights.  Bioware is probably going to have to make their share of the money from a few quick expansion releases followed by a Neverwinter Nights II type release.  So, the outlook is good if Neverwinter Nights sells well and does not take too many returns. <p>- gladimir@san.rr.com<BR><a href=http://www.vagabondia.net/>Vagabondia Online - June 2002</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/uquintrel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quintrel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.lucasarts.com/products/outcast/images/downloads/icons/symbol.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orcan Latrine Digger</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(4/6/02 9:35:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://216.40.197.199/webgraphics/clipart/animals/wolves/clipart_animals_wolves_001.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lots of Discussion on saving Variables</span><hr size=1> Hmph... which is probably why we are now hearing changes in NWN features <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> that will now be in NWN II</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?<br><br><br>Gotta love it. Oh well... not like I won't be buying several copies of NWN any way. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><br><br><div align="right"><font size="5" face="Monotype Corsiva">Quintrel</div><font size="4"><div align="right"><a href="http://www.quintrel.150m.com">Mad Man Extrodinaire</a> </div></font></font><hr size="1" color=#b22222><center>"<i>Opportunity should be equal, must be equal, but achievement must remain individual.<i>"</center><font size="4" face="Monotype Corsiva"><div align="ri